The first object is a cluster of bicycles parked on the sidewalk. While these bicycles are not directly in the path of the vehicle, their presence indicates a potentially high pedestrian area, which adds complexity to the driving environment and may require increased vigilance for pedestrian activity.

Additionally, there's a presence of blurred lights and possibly reflective surfaces on the right side of the image. These high-luminosity indications suggest there might be other vehicles or reflective objects nearby that can be relevant for navigation and require attention for full situational awareness.

Finally, there seems to be debris or objects on the right side of the road, identifiable by irregular shapes and shadows. Autonomous vehicles should note these hazards and ensure they maintain their lane position while keeping a safe distance from such obstacles to avoid potential damage or accidents.
